Name: Harvard University/Soldiers Field Park Garage
Comments: Only Allston and Brighton residents can park at this garage during a snow emergency only. May need to show proof of residency. Parking spots are limited and on a first-come, first-served basis. If parked past the approved the time, may be ticketed/towed.

Name: Lafayette Garage
Comments: Discounted parking is only for Chinatown, Downtown, and North End residents. You need to provide proof of your residency. You will be charged each time your vehicle exits and re-enters the garage.

Name: BPDA/EDIC Garage
Comments: Discounted rate for residents of South Boston only. South Boston Resident Parking Permits are required. Snow Emergency parking is allowed on the fourth floor of the garage only.

Name: Northeastern University/Renaissance Park Garage
Fee: 50% of the variable rate. The most you will pay is $19.00 for each 24-hour period.
Comments: Discounted parking is for Roxbury, South End, and Fenway/Kenmore residents only. Need to have a visible resident parking permit sticker to receive the discount. Parking is based on a first-come basis and depends on the availability of space.

Name: Northeastern University/Gainsboro Garage
Fee: 50% of the variable rate. The most you will pay is $19.00 for each 24-hour period.
Comments: Discounted parking is for Roxbury, South End, and Fenway/Kenmore residents only. Need to have a visible resident parking permit sticker to receive the discount. Parking is based on a first-come basis and depends on the availability of space.

Name: Auditorium Garage
Fee: $11.00 per 24 hours – Snow Emergency parking rate
Comments: Back Bay, Beacon Hill, Chinatown and Beacon Street residents only. Proof of residence, utility bill or RPP sticker.

Name: Shipyard Garage/Mass General Hospital
Comments: Charlestown residents only. Limited space so the garage enforces the 2 hour rule. Anyone who enters more than 2 hours before the Snow Emergency is in effect and/or departs more than 2 hours after the ban has lifted, will not receive the discount rate.

Name: Greenhouse Parking Garage/Ultimate
Comments: Only Back Bay and South End residents can park at the facility. Entrance to the garage is on Cumberland Street. Snow Emergency Parking is limited to 15-20 spaces. Cars must be out within two hours of the ban being lifted or will be charged regular rates.

Name: The Prudential Center Garage
Comments: Discount only for Back Bay, Beacon Hill and South End. If parking ban ends before 6PM residents must move cars within two hours. If ban ends after 6PM residents have till 9AM the following morning to remove cars. Need to stop by level P2 to get discount

Name: LAZ Parking/The Clarendon Parking Garage
Comments: There are a limited amount of public spaces available. Discounted rates for Back Bay, Bay Village, and South End. Proof of residency required. Stop by garage office on first floor of facility to receive the snow emergency rate before leaving vehicle.

Name: Christian Science Garage
Comments: Due to construction, spaces are limited. Call ahead to confirm spaces are still available. Discounted rate for residents of the South End and Back Bay only. Proof of residency is required.

Name: 100 Clarendon Street Garage
Comments: Stop by the garage office on the first floor of the facility to receive the snow emergency rate before leaving with your vehicle. You must show proof of your residency in the Back Bay, South End, or Bay Village.

Name: Channel Center Garage
Comments: Discounted parking for all City of Boston residents. Please bring as proof of residence a valid driverâ€™s license with a City of Boston address to the garage office. You have 24 hours after the City lifts the snow emergency to remove your vehicle.

Name: Crosstown Center Garage
Comments: You must show proof of your Boston residency to the cashier. If you don't, you won't be eligible for the discount.

Name: 200 Stuart Street Garage
Fee: $0 for duration of Snow Emergency for Bay Village residents only. $10/24 hour period for all other Boston residents
Comments: Bay Village resident parking permit or proof of Boston residency is required. To receive the discounted rate, parking can begin two hours before the emergency goes into effect and leave no later than two hours after parking ban is lifted

Name: Motor Mart Garage
Comments: Discounted parking for all Boston residents with a City Of Boston Resident Parking Permit or proof of Boston residency. Enter up to 2 hours before emergency goes into effect and exit within 2 hours of the ban being lifted.

Name: The Alyx Garage
Fee: Snow Emergency rate: $10.00 per day-each new day starts at 5am
Comments: No restrictions, rate available to all parkers.
